# astro-notes

## Bibliography

- **`AstroNotes.bib`** — Zotero Better BibTeX auto-export; do not edit by hand.
- **`sources.bib`** — Manual entries (Astrobites `Amen2026`, books, etc.). Astrobites stay here; Zotero often lacks Astrobites author metadata.
- **`mainNotes.tex`** loads both via `\addbibresource`.
- Use **Zotero/BBT cite keys** in paper notes (e.g. `greenUpperLimitFrequency2025`), not legacy `sources.bib` keys.

## Note scripts & hotkeys (workspace `astro-notes`)

| Task / script | Hotkey | Output |
|---------------|--------|--------|
| New Astrobite | `Ctrl+Shift+A` | `astroBitesNotes/notes/`, `sources.bib` if needed |
| New Paper | `Ctrl+Shift+Alt+P` | `paperNotes/<folder>/`, registers in `paperIncludes.tex` |
| New Paper (Zotero) | task only | Select item in Zotero → cite key + title from BBT JSON-RPC |
| New Glossary | `Ctrl+Shift+G` | `subTex/Astro-glossary.tex`, auto-sorted |

Paper folder default: derived from cite key (`greenUpperLimitFrequency2025` → `greenUpper`), override in prompt if needed.

## Layout

- **Papers:** `\chapter{Title \cite{key}}`, `\section{Abstract}`, bullet list; registered in `paperNotes/paperIncludes.tex` via `\input`. Files use `\ifdefined\AnMainDocument` so the same `.tex` compiles standalone (subfiles) or inside `mainNotes`.
- **Standalone paper build:** task **Build Paper Subfile** or `latexmk -pdf -shell-escape` on the paper `.tex` from its folder.
- **Astrobites:** `\chapter{Title \cite{key} \label{chap:...}}`, section “Abstract and intro”.

## Glossary (`subTex/Astro-glossary.tex`)

- **Acronyms:** `ac:` prefix (`ac:GW`, `ac:TESS`).
- **Observatories:** `obs:` prefix (`obs:Pan-STARRS`).
- **Full terms:** no prefix (`chandrasekhar-limit`, `kilonova`).
- In text: `\gls{key}`. Sort: task **Sort Glossary** or after new entry.

## Build

- Full doc: `latexmk -pdf -shell-escape mainNotes.tex` (tikz externalization, biblatex/biber).
- Use **global** LaTeX Workshop settings; no workspace `settings.json` override here.
- Chapters restart at 1 per `\part` via `\@addtoreset{chapter}{part}`; never `\setcounter{chapter}{0}` in included `.tex` files.

More detail: `memory.md`.
